    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p><b>Description:</b></p>

<p>When performing a horizontal twist while the enemy is moving, a series of incorrect behaviors occurs:</p>

<ul>
	<li>the enemy changes direction</li>
	<li>a sudden displacement occurs (visually resembling teleportation)</li>
	<li>collision detection fails (the enemy may pass through walls or end up inside them)</li>
</ul>


<p>The issue occurs when user input interferes at the moment the enemy's movement is updated.</p>

<p><b>Preconditions:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>Windows Visual Studio is open and running</li>
	<li>The project is open in the editor</li>
	<li>The project configuration selected at startup is Debug</li>
</ul>


<p><b>Steps to reproduce:</b></p>

<ol>
	<li>Launch the emulator with the Pixel Maze game</li>
	<li>Wait for the splash screen</li>
	<li>Perform a twist to start the game</li>
	<li>Wait for the GAME START to finish (3 → 1 → GO)</li>
	<li>Locate the enemy on the game board</li>
	<li>Wait for the enemy to start moving</li>
	<li>While the enemy is moving, perform a horizontal twist on the top edge</li>
	<li>Repeat several times near obstacles</li>
	<li>Observe the enemy’s behavior</li>
</ol>


<p><b>Actual results:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>The enemy changes its direction of movement</li>
	<li>The enemy shifts (teleports)</li>
	<li>The enemy passes through walls or ends up inside them</li>
</ul>


<p><b>Expected results:</b></p>

<ul>
	<li>The enemy’s movement does not depend on player input</li>
	<li>Movement is smooth and predictable</li>
	<li>Collisions are always enforced</li>
	<li>The enemy cannot pass through walls or cross obstacles</li>
</ul>


<p><b>Environment:</b><br/>
Windows 11<br/>
Windows Visual Studio 2022<br/>
Processor: 12th Gen Intel(R) Core(TM) i5-1235U (1.30 GHz)<br/>
RAM: 8.00 GB (available: 7.65 GB)<br/>
System type: 64-bit operating system, x64 processor</p>

<p><b>Severity:</b><br/>
Critical</p>
            <br/>
